{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fc40d8f7-78dc-4ab1-b92a-78113dd3ee98","content":"For a .NET Web API project, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n**Authentication options** (via `--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Example with auth:**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain mydomain.onmicrosoft.com\n```\n\nYou can also add JWT Bearer auth manually via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` for custom identity providers. Want me to scaffold a project with a specific auth setup?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b980b234-508d-4155-ae7b-f13a2f291284","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context with dotnet plugins). I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":265,"requestId":"A815:37B113:C95FB5:E3D4CC:6A027927"},"id":"27cd95a2-2fba-40a4-a846-e17aad5a6f5a","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:49:50.586Z","parentId":"e0baf65e-3c32-4d03-9b7d-47a9872ceaf3"}
